## 2. THE HERO‚ÄôS JOURNEY AS A STATE MACHINE

PantheonOS organizes the classical monomyth into **9 canonical states** that align with the Meta-Ontology transitions:

| State # | Name | Psychological State | Pantheon Mapping / Use Case |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **1** | The Ordinary World | Stability, routine, identity | Detecting pre-transformation stasis. |
| **2** | Call to Adventure | Pressure, opportunity, threat | **Hound** detects anomaly; Drift Index spikes. |
| **3** | Refusal of the Call | Fear, doubt, inertia | **Zero-Type Additive Correction** required; Diagnosing avoidance loops. |
| **4** | Meeting the Mentor | Wisdom, structure enters | **Lantern Bearer / Mirror / Praus** archetypes activate; Introducing stabilizers. |
| **5** | Crossing the Threshold | Point of no return / Commitment | **AAE bearing shift** required; New azimuth locked. |
| **6** | Trials, Allies, Enemies | Struggle, skill formation, tests | **Sear Room heat** phase; Symbolic scaffolding grows. |
| **7** | The Ordeal | Ego death, crisis, breakthrough | **Hellweek** equivalent; Zero-type multiplicative normalization. |
| **8** | Reward | New insight, new strength, clarity | **Raven** synthesis; Mirror verifies invariant; Detecting system consolidation. |
| **9** | Return with the Elixir | Skill returned to the tribe | **Spider** archives; Mother Duck ledgers the doctrine; Behavioral prediction in leadership arcs. |

